##cluster

#
aver_expr_mat <- c()
for(cluster_name in levels(larva@active.ident))
{
  temp <- as.matrix(GetAssayData(larva,slot = "data")[,WhichCells(larva,idents = cluster_name)])
  aver_expr_mat <- cbind(aver_expr_mat,apply(temp,1,mean))
}

colnames(aver_expr_mat) <- levels(larva@active.ident)
#
aver_expr_mat <- aver_expr_mat[larva@assays[["RNA"]]@var.features,]

cormat <- cor(aver_expr_mat)

plot <- pheatmap(cormat, breaks = unique(c(seq(0.6,1, length=100))), color = colorRampPalette(c("blue", "white", "red"))(100),
         border_color = NA, cluster_rows = T, cluster_cols = T, angle_col = 45, main = "correlation_heatmap")

ggsave(filename = paste0("top5Genes",".svg"), device = svg, height = 8, width = 8, plot = plot)

SCENIC

regulonActivity <- read.csv("./SCENIC_result/regulonActivity.csv",row.names = 1)
topTFs <- read.csv("./SCENIC_result/topRegulators.csv")
top5 <- topTFs %>% group_by(seuratCluster) %>% slice_max(n = 5, order_by = RelativeActivity)

#top5
regulonActivity <- regulonActivity[sapply(top5$Regulon, function(e) {which(rownames(regulonActivity) == e)}), ]
#annotation_col <-  data.frame(cluster = factor(top5$seuratCluster), row.names = make.names(top5$Regulon,TRUE)) #make.names

plot <- pheatmap(regulonActivity, breaks = unique(c(seq(-5,5, length=100))), 
                 color = colorRampPalette(c("blue", "white", "red"))(100),
                border_color = NA, cluster_rows = FALSE, cluster_cols = FALSE,
                main = "regulonActivity", show_rownames = F)
plot

ggsave(filename = paste0("regulonActivity",".svg"), device = svg, height = 12, width = 12, plot = plot)
